<div class="comment" id="comment-47770587">
  <div class="comment_head"><a href="/user/MisterTea">MisterTea</a> 19 hours ago</div>
  <div class="comment_text">&gt; The primary goal is clear and simple: to require 3D printer manufacturers to use a state-certified algorithm that checks digital design files for firearm components and blocks print jobs that would produce prohibited parts.<p>&quot;state-certified algorithm&quot; has a really nice tyrannic ring to it. I am sure once this has passed the rich people can finally sleep at night knowing they are safe from roving gangs of armed Mangiones.</div>
